</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umulerin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mulerin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/27/01 10:07:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faydedar gettin nerfed o rsomething.</span><hr size=1> I agree that I don't want to see every 50+ druid with an epic.  However, I do believe that camping for 100+ hours for a random spawn that despawns in 3 hours is a little rediculous.  I guess I don't believe that the only people who should get Faydedar are the ones that have 2 computers, 2 accounts and can be around for days on end w/out taking a break.  Yes, I know of those who haven't camped for long or whatever, but who can deny the majority of those who see faydedar have sat around for 12+ hours in one sitting and are ready to take an uzi to the local minimart out of frustration?  That doesn't make a game fun...<br>
