Mulerin Wulfkin<br>
59th on Karana <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usippylaika.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sippy Laika</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/27/01 1:26:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> &quot;Right.&quot;</span><hr size=1> Karii & Twygg are right. I also think it should remain the way it is now. With only a few easy steps you, too, can get your Epic. These are:<br>
<br>
<br>
First and foremost...<br>
<br>
- Quit your job/school/etc., anything that might require you to leave your PC. Very important!<br>
<br>
<br>
For all us "grouping" Druids...<br>
<br>
- Appologize to all your friends that you can no longer group/raid w/ them anymore because you need to go practice "kiting" to hopefully stand a chance against all those soloing "dr00ds" out there competing for Faydedar. Don't even attempt to answer their confused queries concerning why Faydedar is not a triggered spawn (so that they can all come and assist you now while they are all actually <i>online</i>). Save your breath.<br>
<br>
(<i>Please</i> do not try to contemplate just how a soloing "dr00d" will manage to amasse a force out to TD to help kill the dragon. Instead direct your focus on the intriguing Bermuda Triangle; at least the mystery of how this phenomenon manages to suck people in is easier to understand. Rawr!)<br>
<br>
For practice, I suggest going to Timorous Deep and kiting one of the raptors out in the middle of the ocean. To give some fair semblance of what it will be like kiting Faydedar I suggest snaring yourself first. After 2-3 hours of this take a break, don't wear yourself out. Let your wrist take a rest or the cost of medical treatment will totally outweigh the expected cost of kiting Faydedar.<br>
<br>
<br>
You'll want some insurance to be sure death does not occur, otherwise someone who just watched you die will likely step in and take over. Or worse, Faydedar will despawn. Some in-game items (aside from MR/FR gear which you should already own, unless you're a soloing "dr00d") to help prevent this:<br>
<br>
- Acquire a Fungus Covered Scale Tunic. After kiting Faydedar for several hours (and of course factoring in lag/warping/etc.) you're bound to take a few nasty hits and won't be able to stop and heal yourself. This will help. (Approx. cost 40,000-50,000 platinum pieces.) Easy.<br>
<br>
- Acquire a Shrunken Goblin Skull Earring. It has an instant cast of "Grim Aura." Yes, the effect is useless to a Druid but it does give you a junk buff for Faydedar's dispelling. (Approx. cost 5,000-10,000 platinum pieces.) Easy.<br>
<br>
- Camp the AC, and do the Jboots quest. Yes, you can cast sow but you won't have time to do so when Faydedar dispells you and starts beating/breathing on you. Just skip a night's sleep in the hopes that no one is camping it the wee hours of the morning (not likely), or you can just be a "dr00d" and <i>take</i> the AC when it spawns. Piece of cake.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you plan on sitting in Timorous Deep yourself...<br>
<br>
- Run out to your nearest quality office supply store and purchase a really comfortable chair. You're going to be sitting for a <i>very</i> long time. Don't skim. (Approx. cost $99-200.)<br>
<br>
- On the way home from the office supply store you will want to stop by EB and pick up a brand new PS/2 w/ a few games. You won't be playing EQ so might as well. (Approx. cost $299 w/ games $400-500.)<br>
 <br>
<br>
There is an alternative to this:<br>
<br>
- Visit www.dell.com and purchase a 2nd PC for the explicit purpose of camping a "dummy" character in TD to camp for you. A little more costly but will actually allow you to play the game while you wait. (Approx. cost $899-1500 does not include shipping costs to your state, or applicable taxes. Approx. cost for 2nd copy of EQ $29 + $10/mo. for 2nd account.)<br>
<br>
<br>
Before I forget...<br>
<br>
- Stock up on antacids of your choice. I would highly suggest a month's supply worth. The constant stress of knowing that the moment Faydedar spawns a dozen or so Druids will suddenly appear in a furious frenzy and attempt to KS each other will eat a hole right through your stomach. (Approx. cost $10-35.) Valium(tm) can also be substituted, but may impair your ability to drive. See your Doctor for prescription.<br>
<br>
- Invest in a lucky charm. Rabbit Foot, Horse Shoe, Dashboard Dancing Hula Girl, whatever. I cannot stress how important this is. You'll need all the luck you can get to avoid Faydedar finally spawning after your 200+ hour camp only for it to be at four in the morning when everyone you know is in bed, <i>asleep</i> (where you should be).<br>
<br>
<br>
And last, but not least...<br>
<br>
- Throw out all your RPing sentiments toward this game. After all, there isn't anything RP-ish about doing any of the above, now is there?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
